The Director-General, National Youth Service Corps (NYSC), Brigadier General Suleiman Kazaure said no corps member will be posted to areas facing security challenges. A statement by the NYSC Director, Press and Public Relations, Mrs Adenike Adeyemi, said Kazaure made the declaration yesterday at Ogun State Orientation Camp, Sagamu, while addressing the 2018 Batch ‘A’ corps members. He said the management of NYSC has put necessary machinery in place to ensure safety of all corps members, while warning corps member not to engage in activities that could endanger their safety. Kazaure enjoined corps members to uphold the ideals of patriotism as responsible citizens in the discharge of their duties during primary assignment. The Ogun State Coordinator of NYSC, Mr John Okpo said a total of 2,513 corps members registered for the orientation course.